Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.54,0:13:26.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这双手已经真切地触到了地狱\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}These hands have actually touched hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.62,0:13:30.82,正片中文,,0,0,0,,而且它们依然炙烤着我\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And they burn me still.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.09,0:13:36.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是宏大的仪式会停止吗\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}But the grand rite was averted?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.26,0:13:45.90,正片中文,,0,0,0,,确实是只有一种方法可以停止那个宏大的仪式\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}There really is only one way to stop the grand rite.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.90,0:13:49.97,正片中文,,0,0,0,,必须要有一个人在月亮升起，仪式结束以前\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}One must kill the witch that began it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:53.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,杀了开启仪式的巫师\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}before the moonrise that ends it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.61,0:13:55.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在这种情况下\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}In this case
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.01,0:13:57.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,杀了约翰 奥尔登\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}kill John Alden.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.06,0:14:11.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,众人皆知\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}It's no secret
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.33,0:14:16.60,正片中文,,0,0,0,,约翰 奥尔登对我们有着冷酷而坚定的仇恨\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}that John Alden has a cold and a willful hatred for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.60,0:14:18.80,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就因为我们所信仰的一切\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}for everything we believe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.80,0:14:23.07,正片中文,,0,0,0,,以及我们圣徒组成的清教徒团体\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}and for our puritan community of saints.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.07,0:14:24.67,正片中文,,0,0,0,,正是由此\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And so, it was
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.67,0:14:29.44,正片中文,,0,0,0,,年轻的约翰 奥尔登才与塞勒姆切断联系\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}that a young John Alden severed himself from Salem
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.44,0:14:35.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,并怀着一颗没有留恋 没有信仰 没有爱的心\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}and, rootless, faithless, and loveless,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.42,0:14:39.25,正片中文,,0,0,0,,投身到了战争的残酷考验中\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}cast himself into the crucible of war,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.25,0:14:41.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,结果他在战争中被野蛮的印第安人俘虏\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}where he was captured by the heathen Indians.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.19,0:14:47.39,正片中文,,0,0,0,,从此他心中邪恶的种子 已经长出了一个坚硬而恶毒的外壳的种子\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And that seed of evil within, already a hard and vicious knot,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.40,0:14:50.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,找到了茁壮成长的沃土\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}found fertile ground in which to flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.50,0:14:55.27,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那些愤怒恐怖的神灵的野蛮奴仆们\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And the savage servants of the angry, eldritch gods,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.27,0:14:58.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他们将奥尔登视作来自撒旦的礼物\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}they saw in Alden a gift from Satan,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.81,0:15:00.51,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一件充满能量又邪恶\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}a powerful and vicious weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.51,0:15:03.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在他们绝望的战争中用来对付我们的武器\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}to be used in their hopeless war against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.91,0:15:07.48,正片中文,,0,0,0,,所以 因为他对我们的仇恨\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And so, because of his hatred for us
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.48,0:15:13.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,对一个背叛了他的人的仇恨\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}and his hatred for one he felt had betrayed him,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.32,0:15:15.36,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他的确变成了一件充满能量而又邪恶的武器\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}a powerful and a vicious weapon he became.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:19.26,正片中文,,0,0,0,,先生 这纯粹是想象\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Sir, this is pure fancy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.26,0:15:21.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,赤裸裸的臆想\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}bald conjecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:22.06,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你根本不知道那些\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}You have no idea what may
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.06,0:15:23.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,曾经发生在奥尔登长官身上的事\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}or may not have happened to Captain Alden
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.57,0:15:27.60,正片中文,,0,0,0,,无论是在他为我们所有人的生命而与印第安人奋战时的事\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}while fighting for all our lives against the Indians
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.60,0:15:29.74,正片中文,,0,0,0,,还是他被印第安人俘虏时的事\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}or when he was held their captive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.74,0:15:31.97,正片中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 那么 让他说说看\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Well, then, let him speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.97,0:15:33.41,正片中文,,0,0,0,,让奥尔登在这里现在就告诉我们\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Let Alden tell us here and now
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.41,0:15:36.88,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你在野蛮人的领地里失踪了那么久\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}exactly what transpired during that long period of time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.88,0:15:38.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,到底发生了什么事情\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}when you were lost amongst the savages.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.98,0:15:40.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,说啊 你\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Speak, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.55,0:15:43.38,正片中文,,0,0,0,,说啊\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Speak!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.32,0:15:46.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不说吗\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}No?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.22,0:15:51.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那么多年 他干了什么呢\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}All those years, what could he have been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.16,0:15:53.59,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我来告诉你们\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}I will tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.60,0:15:55.10,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就像约伯记中所写的撒旦一样\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Like Satan in the book of job,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.10,0:15:57.76,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他在土地上来回地走动\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}he was walking to and fro upon the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.77,0:16:00.80,正片中文,,0,0,0,,操纵着怨恨的工具\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}mastering the tools of malice,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.80,0:16:02.54,正片中文,,0,0,0,,学习着黑暗的法术\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}learning the dark art
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.54,0:16:07.24,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这些法术让他可以远距离地派遣魔鬼的巫使听他的指令\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}of sending demonic familiars to do his bidding at a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.24,0:16:10.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你们可以观察到 这儿 在他的脖子上\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}You will observe, here, upon his neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.41,0:16:16.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,有一块像铁一样坚硬 并有一个洞的肿块\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}An iron-hard, raised lump with a hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.95,0:16:21.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他就是通过这儿喂养他的巫使\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}and it was here where he suckles his familiars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.20,0:16:31.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这是你最后一次笑了\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}You will not laugh again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.40,0:16:34.10,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我敢保证你已经笑了很多次\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}I'm sure you have laughed many times to think how,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.10,0:16:37.67,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就在这位忠诚的年轻妻子的面前\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}beneath the very nose of a devoted young wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.67,0:16:41.17,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你想着怎么把我们的领导者 曾经充满活力的乔治 西布利\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}you turned our leader, a once robust George Sibley,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.18,0:16:44.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,推进痛苦的折磨中的时候\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}into a suffering heap that he is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.05,0:16:47.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在你摧毁了我们社区的顶梁柱之后\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And after you had undermined the pillar of our community,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.82,0:16:50.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你发动了一场恐怖战役\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}you unleashed a campaign of terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:55.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就是奥尔登带来了幽灵的恐惧 黑夜的女巫\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}It was Alden who projected that specter of dread, the night hag,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.56,0:16:57.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,来恐吓默茜 露易丝\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}to terrorize Mercy Lewis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.19,0:17:00.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你们会问 为什么 为什么是默茜 露易丝\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And you will ask, "Why? Why Mercy Lewis?"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.56,0:17:04.97,正片中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 可能是因为她的父亲 好人牧师露易丝\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Well, perhaps it was because her father, the good Reverend Lewis,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.97,0:17:09.30,正片中文,,0,0,0,,娶了奥尔登那苦恋而未得到的情人\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}married Alden's bitterly lost love to a hated rival,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.30,0:17:15.34,正片中文,,0,0,0,,又或者只是为了表明塞勒姆镇无人能够幸免\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}or perhaps it was just to show that no one in Salem is safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.34,0:17:19.25,正片中文,,0,0,0,,即便她是牧师的女儿\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}not even the daughter of a blessed Reverend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.55,0:17:23.92,正片中文,,0,0,0,,柯顿\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Cotton!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:25.65,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你照顾过默茜 露易丝\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}You attended Mercy Lewis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.65,0:17:30.26,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你对她的艰难处境没有怀疑\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}You had no doubt as to what ailed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.26,0:17:33.03,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她确实是受到了幽灵的攻击\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}She was indeed under spectral attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.03,0:17:34.13,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是奥尔顿长官\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}but Captain Alden --
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.13,0:17:36.33,正片中文,,0,0,0,,奥尔顿长官 他说什么\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Captain Alden -- what did he say
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.33,0:17:38.33,正片中文,,0,0,0,,当他看到如此的攻击时\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}when he witnessed such an attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.10,0:17:42.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他对此有些怀疑\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}He cast some doubt upon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.64,0:17:44.94,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一些怀疑\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Some doubt!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.94,0:17:47.17,正片中文,,0,0,0,,有人告诉我\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}I am told...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.17,0:17:49.41,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他说它是\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}He said it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.41,0:17:51.44,正片中文,,0,0,0,,屁\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}"Bullshit."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.51,0:17:55.85,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他还说祈祷是没有用的\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And he said that prayers were worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.85,0:17:59.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,祈祷 无用\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Prayer? Worthless?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.42,0:18:03.39,正片中文,,0,0,0,,问问你们自己\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Ask yourselves --
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.39,0:18:06.53,正片中文,,0,0,0,,每次我们意图抓住和阻止一个巫师时\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}every time we have attempted to catch and stop a witch,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.53,0:18:09.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是谁站出来保护他们\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}who has risen up to defend them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.50,0:18:13.60,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是独自混在我们之中 一次又一次地和我们作对\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Who alone among us, in encounter, time after time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.60,0:18:16.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,而巫术对他总是毫发无伤\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}with witches has emerged with nary a scratch upon him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.64,0:18:20.37,正片中文,,0,0,0,,当乔治 西布利死的时候他说了谁的名字\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Whose name was on Giles Corey's lips as he died?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.37,0:18:25.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,谁宣称他在坟墓中能够看到在座的每个人\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Who has proclaimed that he will see every man here in his grave?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.05,0:18:27.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,又是谁 甚至在明明她创造出的怪物时\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And who stood up to defend Bridget bishop
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.62,0:18:31.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,也出头保护布里吉特主教\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}even in the very sight of the monstrosity she had created?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.42,0:18:32.72,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我向你们发誓\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}I swear to you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.72,0:18:36.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这个人每次开口 都是对自己的谴责\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}this man condemns himself every time he opens his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.89,0:18:39.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就像撒旦在伊甸园中\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}And like Satan in the garden of eden,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.93,0:18:43.10,正片中文,,0,0,0,,约翰 奥尔登明白女人们\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}John Alden understands that women are the open doorway
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.10,0:18:47.07,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是邪恶得以毒害我们的通道\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}through which evil enters to poison us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.07,0:18:51.70,正片中文,,0,0,0,,多少女性 年轻或年老的 好的或坏的\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}How many women, young and old, good and bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.71,0:18:53.51,正片中文,,0,0,0,,都被奥尔登迷惑了\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}has Alden bewitched?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.51,0:18:57.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,有人见到约翰 奥尔登甚至想勾引\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}It has been seen that John Alden attempted to seduce
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.01,0:19:00.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这里最高贵的女性\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}even the highest women in the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.28,0:19:01.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,玛丽 西布利\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Mary Sibley.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.35,0:19:06.29,正片中文,,0,0,0,,被告是否强行进入了你的房子\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Did not the accused forcibly enter your house,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.29,0:19:10.72,正片中文,,0,0,0,,而且 竟然还进入了你的闺房 就是在那个死亡的夜晚\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}nay, into your very boudoir, in the dead of night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.73,0:19:13.03,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我会允许那种事情吗\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Would I allow such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.03,0:19:15.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.66,0:19:18.73,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是你的仆人已经证实了\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}But your servant man has testified
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.73,0:19:22.87,正片中文,,0,0,0,,奥尔登在那天晚上确实强行进入了你的房子\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}that Alden did indeed forcibly make entry in the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.34,0:19:29.31,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他来讨论政治\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}He came to discuss politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.31,0:19:30.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,- 政治 - 确实\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}- Politics? - Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.84,0:19:31.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他来阐述他的意图\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}To announce his intention
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.98,0:19:34.18,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他想在选举理事会里得到他父亲的席位\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}to take his father's seat on the select board.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.18,0:19:35.65,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在半夜吗\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}In the middle of the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.42,0:19:42.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,黑尔小姐\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}Miss Hale.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.69,0:19:49.10,正片中文,,0,0,0,,被告被发现在公共场合强吻你\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}The accused was seen kissing you forcibly in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.10,0:19:51.63,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这不是你的错\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}There is no blame attached to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.63,0:19:55.97,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你只是一个 一个柔弱又没有反抗能力的姑娘\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}You are a -- a slight and defenseless slip of a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.97,0:19:58.47,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是你否认这个吗\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}But do you deny it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.42,0:20:08.12,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不否认\N{\3c&H0000000&\fs30}He did.
